	<Title>
		Ordering a meatless meal? Skip the fat
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Most restaurants offer meatless selections. You can even find vegetarian fare at many fast-food places. But if you&apos;re ordering a meatless meal, make sure your selection isn&apos;t filled with fat and calories. Avoid veggie items that are loaded with high-fat cheese. Choose condiments that are lower in fat, such as mustard or low-fat mayo. If you don&apos;t see a vegetarian selection on the menu, ask the server if you can place a special order.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Body>
